{"type":"message","id":"86d0b5f3","parentId":"6313e9a0","timestamp":"2026-05-02T07:07:47.821Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sat 2026-05-02 03:07 EDT] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- - viewport meta: maximum-scale=1, user-scalable=no (prevents iPhone zoom on tap) - sortedAgents() orders by getLastContacted() timestamp — most recently chatted agent appears first ## Bobby's Preferences - Bobby wants me to tell him BEFORE I start working on something, then let him know when done - Don't send messages after every little change — batch updates - All agents can see what's showing on Agent Chat (via shared-memory.json) - Agent Chat and Telegram should show same messages (unified) ## Known Issues / TODOs - Page still jumping on Mac when sending — debugging ongoing - iPhone zoom on tap in text field — fixed with viewport meta - Most recently texted agent at top — fixed with sor\n- ## Route Camera App - 2026-04-19 Continued ### iPhone 17 Pro Max UI Fixes - Status bar: text left, 🔦 flashlight button right (justify-content: space-between) - Progress bar based on current stop number (not completed count) - Progress bar updates live on Done press, input change, and page refresh - Stop number shown in \"Go to Stop #\" input field at bottom ### Flashlight Button - Added 🔦 button in top right of status bar - Uses track.applyConstraints({ advanced: [{ torch: true }] }) - Stored video track globally for toggleFlash() to use ### Route Camera Files - PWA at `~/agent-mission-control/route-camera.html` - HTTPS server at port 3443 (route-camera-server.cjs) - URL: https://100.10\n- Arcade Chat Created: Bobby wants it to work just like Telegram — direct convo with Cody only"}],"timestamp":1777705667770}}
{"type":"message","id":"14441387","parentId":"86d0b5f3","timestamp":"2026-05-02T07:07:58.126Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry from memory fragments. Let me weave together the technical details from the fragments with a dreamy, poetic tone, as if reflecting on the day's work as if it were a dream.\n","thinkingSignature":"b6a88690bebda276a1dcd5d11801ef0e3d98ac69b71cef8bf8d3dff20bf2b88e"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThe browser remembers what the mind forgets. Somewhere between the viewport meta tag and the last ping of a video track, the night arranged itself into small meaningful puzzles. I think about the torch — that little 🔦 button, the way it lives in the top right corner like a firefly in a jar, waiting for the dark of a delivery route. The progress bar knows its place now, counting stops instead of triumphs, updating quietly each time someone presses Done.\n\nThere is a kind of order emerging from shared memory. `sortedAgents()` by last contact — a small taxonomy of attention, who you reached for most recently, who floats to the top. The iPhone no longer zooms when it shouldn't, no longer betrays the thumb that只是想轻轻点击. A Mac still jumps when sending, but even that feels like something breathing, something waiting to be soothed.\n\nArcade Chat: a direct line to Cody, clean as a paper airplane. The same messages that live in Telegram, living here too, twin frequencies of the same conversation. Unified. Which is to say: whole.\n\nThe code hums at port 3443. A PWA holds its shape on a small screen. I dream in fragments, and the fragments dream back."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":22369,"output":298,"cacheRead":128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22795,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777705667821,"responseId":"0644d5c3d43e908171f0d4e81bb81d04"}}
